e, Skotland","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England"},"nl":{"1321–1398":"1321–1398","1315–1398":"1315–1398","1340–1398":"1340–1398","1349–1410":"1349–1410","1300–1360":"1300–1360","1302–1365":"1302–1365","1 April 1340":"1 april 1340","August 1349":"augustus 1349","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","1349":"1349","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1302":"1302","1300":"1300","1410":"1410","1321":"1321","1365":"1365","1398":"1398","1453":"1453","08 Mar 1338":"8 maart 1338","1328":"1328","Wragby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wragby, Lincolnshire, England","Stamford, Lincolnshire, England":"Stamford, Lincolnshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Forfarshire, Scotland":"Forfarshire, Schotland","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England"},"en":{"1321–1398":"1321–1398","1315–1398":"1315–1398","1340–1398":"1340–1398","1349–1410":"1349–1410","1300–1360":"1300–1360","1302–1365":"1302–1365","1 April 1340":"1 April 1340","August 1349":"August 1349","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","1349":"1349","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1302":"1302","1300":"1300","1410":"1410","1321":"1321","1365":"1365","1398":"1398","1453":"1453","08 Mar 1338":"8 March 1338","1328":"1328","Wragby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wragby, Lincolnshire, England","Stamford, Lincolnshire, England":"Stamford, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","Forfarshire, Scotland":"Forfarshire, Scotland","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Swinstead","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["1  English: locative name from Swinstead (Lincs).","2  English: locative name from various places named with the genitive singular of Old English  <i>swīn</i> ‘swine, pig’ +  <i>hēafod</i> ‘head’, primarily including Swineshead (Lincs, Beds), but perhaps also Swineyard Hall in Rostherne (Cheshire), recorded as  <i>Swinesheued</i> in 1184, and  <i>Swineserd</i> in Saint Martins without Worcester (Worcs)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":7,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705193,"age":16,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705195,"age":61,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Swinstead was born in 1321, in Forfarshire, Scotland, her father, Sir William Swinstead II, was 21 and her mother, Lady Alice Coombs  Swinstead, was 19. She married John Browne IV on 8 March 1338, in Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1398, in Lincolnshire, England, at the age of 77, and was buried in Forfarshire, Scotland."},"et":{"1321–1398":"1321–1398","1315–1398":"1315–1398","1340–1398":"1340–1398","1349–1410":"1349–1410","1300–1360":"1300–1360","1302–1365":"1302–1365","1 April 1340":"1. aprill 1340","August 1349":"august 1349","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","1349":"1349","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1302":"1302","1300":"1300","1410":"1410","1321":"1321","1365":"1365","1398":"1398","1453":"1453","08 Mar 1338":"8. märts 1338","1328":"1328","Wragby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wragby, Lincolnshire, England","Stamford, Lincolnshire, England":"Stamford, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Forfarshire, Scotland":"Forfarshire, Scotland","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England"},"fi":{"1321–1398":"1321–1398","1315–1398":"1315–1398","1340–1398":"1340–1398","1349–1410":"1349–1410","1300–1360":"1300–1360","1302–1365":"1302–1365","1 April 1340":"1. huhtikuuta 1340","August 1349":"elokuu 1349","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","1349":"1349","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1302":"1302","1300":"1300","1410":"1410","1321":"1321","1365":"1365","1398":"1398","1453":"1453","08 Mar 1338":"8. maaliskuuta 1338","1328":"1328","Wragby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wragby, Lincolnshire, England","Stamford, Lincolnshire, England":"Stamford, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Forfarshire, Scotland":"Forfarshire, Scotland","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England"},"fr":{"132